l,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"201(f)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"10:6915(f).","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"14:758a(f).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"[None.]","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"[None.]","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"201(g)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"37:232(c) (less last sentence).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-10-12/ch681/s201/c"},"text":"Oct. 12, 1949, ch. 681, § 201(c)","children":[],"tail":" (less last sentence), "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/807"},"text":"63 Stat. 807","children":[],"tail":"; redesignated as “(c)” by "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1955-03-31/ch20/s2/2"},"text":"Mar. 31, 1955, ch. 20, § 2(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/69/19"},"text":"69 Stat. 19","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"May 20, 1958","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/422/s1/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–422, § 1(3)","children":[],"tail":" (first sentence), "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/72/124"},"text":"72 Stat. 124","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a), the words “whether under temporary or permanent appointment” are omitted as surplusage. The words “the following pay grades” are substituted for the words “the various pay grades prescribed for commissioned officers by subsection (a) of this section, as follows”. The words “(other than a commissioned warrant officer)” are inserted to conform to the definition of “warrant officer” in section 101(13) of this revised title.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (b), the words “with two or less years of service computed under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t37/s205"},"text":"section 205 of this title","children":[],"tail":"” are substituted for the word “minimum”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsections (c) and (e), the words “with two or less years of service computed under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t37/s205"},"text":"section 205 of this title","children":[],"tail":"” are substituted for the words “with under two cumulative years’ service” and “with under two cumulative years of service”, in sections 308 and 232(e), respectively, of existing title 37."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (e), the words “enlisted or appointed under the Army Aviation Cadet Act, as amended, or under the Naval Aviation Cadet Act of 1942, as amended” are omitted as obsolete and surplusage. Both of the cited acts were repealed by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041/s53"},"text":"section 53 of the Act of August 10, 1956, ch. 1041","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70A/641"},"text":"70A Stat. 641","children":[],"tail":"), and replaced by various sections of title 10. Further reference is surplusage, however, since aviation cadets are not appointed or enlisted under any provision of law other than the sections of title 10 embodying the former Army Aviation Cadet Act and the Naval Aviation Cadet Act of 1942. The word “basic” is inserted for clarity, since the word “pay” as defined in section 101(21) of this revised title includes special and incentive pays. Incentive pay for aviation cadets is provided in section 301(b) of this revised title."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (f), the words “While on active duty”, in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s6915/f"},"text":"section 6915(f) of title 10","children":[],"tail":" and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t14/s758a/f"},"text":"section 758a(f) of title 14","children":[],"tail":", are omitted as covered by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t37/s204"},"text":"section 204 of this title","children":[],"tail":" which prescribes the conditions under which members of the uniformed services are entitled to basic pay. The words “Unless he is entitled to the basic pay of a higher pay grade” are substituted for the words “or that of his grade, whichever is greater” in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s6915/f"},"text":"section 6915(f) of title 10","children":[],"tail":" and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t14/s758a/f"},"text":"section 758a(f) of title 14","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (g), the words “Except as provided by subsections (e) and (f)” are inserted to reflect those subsections relating to enlisted aviation cadets or aviation pilots.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb057831c-2930-11f1-a69d-9cbca84c43f0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idb057831d-2930-11f1-a69d-9cbca84c43f0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2025—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/119/60"},"text":"Pub. L. 119–60","children":[],"tail":" struck out par. (1) designation, substituted “For the” for “Subject to paragraph (2), for the” and, in the heading of the second column of the table, “Marine Corps, and Space Force” for “and Marine Corps”, and struck out par. (2) which read as follows: “For the purpose of computing their basic pay, commissioned officers of the Space Force are assigned to the pay grades in the table in paragraph (1) by grade or rank in the Air Force that is equivalent to the grade or rank in which such officers are serving in the Space Force.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2021—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283","children":[],"tail":" designated existing provisions as par. (1), substituted “Subject to paragraph (2), for the purpose” for “For the purpose”, and added par. (2)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2006—Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/163"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–163","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Navy Reserve” for “Naval Reserve”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1991—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/190/s1111/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–190, § 1111(b)","children":[],"tail":", amended table generally, adding provisions relating to Chief Warrant Officer at grade W–5."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/190/s605"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–190, § 605","children":[],"tail":", amended subsec. (c) generally. Prior to amendment, subsec. (c) read as follows: “An aviation cadet of the Navy, Air Force, Marine Corps, or Coast Guard is entitled to monthly basic pay at the rate of 50 percent of the basic pay of a commissioned officer in pay grade O–1 with two or less years of service computed under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t37/s205"},"text":"section 205 of this title","children":[],"tail":".”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/25"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–25","children":[],"tail":" struck out “of this section” after “subsections (c) and (d)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1990—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/502"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–502","children":[],"tail":" inserted “Assistant Secretary for Health” in fourth column of table in pay grade O–10."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1985—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/145"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–145","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Rear admiral (lower half)” for “Commodore” in third column of table in pay grade O–7."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1984—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/557"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–557","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Rear admiral” for “Rear admiral (Navy) and Rear admiral (upper half)(Coast Guard and National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration)” in third column of table in pay grade O–8, and in pay grade O–7 substituted “Commodore” for “Commodore (Navy) and Rear admiral (lower half) and commodore (Coast Guard and National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1983—Subsecs. (b) to (f). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/94"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–94","children":[],"tail":" struck out subsec. (b) which related to basic pay for contract surgeons, redesignated subsecs. (c) to (f) as (b) to (e), respectively, and in subsec. (e), as so redesignated, substituted “subsections (c) and (d)” for “subsections (d) and (e)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1981—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/86"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–86","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Commodore” for “Commodore admiral” in third column of table in pay grade O–7."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1980—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/513/s506/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–513, § 506(3)","children":[],"tail":", substituted in heading of third column of table “National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration” for “Environmental Science Services Administration” and in third column “Rear admiral (Navy) and Rear admiral (upper half) (Coast Guard and National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration)” for “Rear admiral (upper half)” and “Commodore admiral (Navy) and Rear admiral (lower half) and commodore (Coast Guard and National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration)” for “Rear admiral (lower half) and commodore”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (f). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/513/s516/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–513, § 516(2)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “subsection (d)” for “subsection (f)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1979—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/76"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–76","children":[],"tail":" transferred the Surgeon General from pay grade O–8 to pay grade O–9 in fourth column of table."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1977—Subsecs. (c) to (g). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/79"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–79","children":[],"tail":" struck out subsec. (c) which related to the monthly rate of pay of cadets and midshipmen at the service academies, and redesignated subsecs. (d) to (g) as (c) to (f), respectively."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1970—Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/278"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–278","children":[],"tail":" entitled aviation cad